    "name": "Pattern of Procrastination (PoP)",
    "summary": "A framework for understanding the recurring patterns and triggers behind procrastination.",
    "explanation": "The Pattern of Procrastination (PoP) framework helps identify and understand your personal procrastination triggers. Rather than treating procrastination as a character flaw, it examines the patterns: What types of tasks do you avoid? When does procrastination peak? What emotions precede it? By mapping your procrastination patterns, you can design targeted interventions - breaking tasks into smaller pieces, addressing emotional blocks, or restructuring your environment. Understanding your PoP transforms procrastination from an enemy into diagnostic information.",
